This paper discusses a framework for detecting phishing emails using machine learning techniques such as neural networks and fuzzy logic. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the software engineering aspects of the proposed framework, which could make it relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, since phishing attacks are a type of cybercrime, the paper could also belong to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
